{"kind":"blogger#post","id":"8127243455080655569","blog":{"id":"2360593805083673688"},"published":"2011-12-02T07:57:00-08:00","updated":"2011-12-02T07:57:57-08:00","url":"http://www.quietlikehorses.com/2011/12/easy-diy-advent-calendar.html","selfLink":"https://www.googleapis.com/blogger/v3/blogs/2360593805083673688/posts/8127243455080655569","title":"Easy DIY Advent Calendar","content":"<div class=\"separator\" style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-Pojg7rwqIpA/Ttjxy5WZ3sI/AAAAAAAAMag/R8febUL3zw8/s1600/DIY+advent+calendar+1.jpg\" imageanchor=\"1\" style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\"><img border=\"0\" src=\"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-Pojg7rwqIpA/Ttjxy5WZ3sI/AAAAAAAAMag/R8febUL3zw8/s1600/DIY+advent+calendar+1.jpg\" /></a><a href=\"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-jzYhZRDeikM/TtjxxtqjFdI/AAAAAAAAMaY/npQUgg5a7zU/s1600/DIY+advent+calendar+2.jpg\" imageanchor=\"1\" style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\"><img border=\"0\" src=\"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-jzYhZRDeikM/TtjxxtqjFdI/AAAAAAAAMaY/npQUgg5a7zU/s1600/DIY+advent+calendar+2.jpg\" /></a></div><br />\n<div class=\"separator\" style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-GLIizBZUi90/TtjxzjEqUlI/AAAAAAAAMao/OCNeSSFscaU/s1600/DIY+advent+calendar+3.jpg\" imageanchor=\"1\" style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\"><img border=\"0\" src=\"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-GLIizBZUi90/TtjxzjEqUlI/AAAAAAAAMao/OCNeSSFscaU/s1600/DIY+advent+calendar+3.jpg\" /></a></div>One of my favorite things about Christmas are the advent calendars. This year I made a really simple one from paper treat bags I found at Michaels. I used stencils to outline numbers on each bag from 1 to 25. Then I carefully painted glue over the outlined numbers and sprinkled glitter on top. I strung them all up on the mantel using a bit of twine and clipped them on with mini clothespins.<br />\n<br />\nAlan and I are taking turns filling each bag with a surprise for the other person. I'm taking the odd days and Alan's taking the evens. On the first day, I hid some of his <a href=\"http://bit.ly/sQ0msd\" target=\"_blank\">favorite cookies</a> inside. On the second day, I got a handwritten poem and...software! Sweet and practical at the same time :)","author":{"id":"06629562195146939698","displayName":"Sobrina Tung","url":"http://www.blogger.com/profile/06629562195146939698","image":{"url":"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_mkw1MyhyGTY/TI8X4CO5nWI/AAAAAAAAERk/4p5D74gYdFE/S45/me.JPG"}},"replies":{"totalItems":"5","selfLink":"https://www.googleapis.com/blogger/v3/blogs/2360593805083673688/posts/8127243455080655569/comments"},"labels":["To See"]}